Package: idiographic
Type: Package
Title: Network Estimation from Intensive Longitudinal Data
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: person("Mohammed", "Saqr", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
    email = "mohammed.saqr@uef.fi")
Author: Mohammed Saqr [aut, cre, cph]
Maintainer: Mohammed Saqr <mohammed.saqr@uef.fi>
Description: Person-specific and within-person network estimation from
    intensive longitudinal and panel data. Provides preprocessing audits,
    edge-stability diagnostics, model-comparison reports, rolling forecast
    validation, rolling ordinary and graphical vector autoregression, ordinary
    vector autoregression (VAR), graphical vector autoregression (graphical
    VAR), multilevel vector autoregression (mlVAR), native Bayesian VAR and
    multilevel VAR validated statistically against selected frozen 'Mplus'
    Dynamic Structural Equation Modeling (DSEM) outputs without requiring
    'Mplus', unified
    Structural Equation Modeling (uSEM), and Group Iterative Multiple Model
    Estimation (GIMME).
    Graphical VAR follows Epskamp et al. (2018)
    <doi:10.1080/00273171.2018.1454823>; GIMME follows Gates and Molenaar
    (2012) <doi:10.1016/j.neuroimage.2012.06.026>. Idiographic supervised
    machine-learning models are available through fit_ml(), using native
    base-R algorithms. Results have tidy accessors and optional network
    plotting support.
